song_name: No Way To Treat A Friend

version_description: A fairly accurate transcription taken from a live performance on Youtube. Feel free to edit and improve.
This version uses the chords from the song's sheet music. There are a lot of intimidating-sounding chord names but their forms are not too difficult and patterns quickly emerge.
Basic chord progression: Am C G F https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2CZtctVMg8s Amy has played this solo on guitar a couple of times with capo on 5.
Tune your low E string down to D to play this.
Emily plays this with capo on 4 and picks some complex chords. This is Amy's guitar part from the "Become You" songbook. It's much more simple.
The tuning suggests EADFAD but the highest 3 strings aren't used.
Tuning: DADGBC. This song is picked by Emily. Sounds nice gently strummed though.
Simple chords but effective. Chords taken from Amy's written notes from the Behind the Scenes video.

Tune B string down to A. Very complex song. For the bridge, the lines overlap with up to 3 being sung at once. I've given the chords for each line individually. At the end, I've written out the Carry my mother... part separately from the chorus. I hope that makes sense.
